
> Section 1 - emote
>
> emote <action>
>
> This causes your character to emote an action; this may be abbreviated
> to ':<action>'.
> You may also use ;, which emotes an action, but with no space after
> your name.  For Example: the command ':'s box is big.' produces
> '<yourname>'s box is big.'.
>
> emote is functionally equivalent to pose.
>
> See Also: pose(1), say(1)

